query.result:
1 When he who lights up all the world 2 descends from our hemisphere, 3 so that the day on every side is consumed,
4 the sky, which is first ignited by him alone, 5 suddenly remakes itself seemingly 6 through many lights, in which one shines;
7 this act of the sky came to my mind, 8 as the sign of the world and of its leaders 9 was silent in the blessed beak;
10 because all those living lights, 11 shining much more, began songs 12 fragile and fleeting from my memory.

